import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.scatter(series_data['X'], series_data['Y'], label=series)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.groupby('Series').agg({'X': ['mean', 'std'], 'Y': ['mean', 'std']})
    data.columns = ['_'.join(col).strip() for col in data.columns.values]
    data = data.reset_index()
    x = data['Series']
    y1 = data['X_mean']
    y2 = data['Y_mean']
    y3 = data['X_std']
    y4 = data['Y_std']
    plt.bar(x, y1, yerr=y3, label='X')
    plt.bar(x, y2, yerr=y4, label='Y')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.hist(series_data['X'], alpha=0.5, label=f'{series} X')
        plt.hist(series_data['Y'], alpha=0.5, label=f'{series} Y')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['X'], data['Y'], label='Series I', marker='o', linestyle='None')
    plt.plot(data['X.1'], data['Y.1'], label='Series II', marker='o', linestyle='None')
    plt.plot(data['X.2'], data['Y.2'], label='Series III', marker='o', linestyle='None')
    plt.plot(data['X.3'], data['Y.3'], label='Series IV', marker='o', linestyle='None')
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y across all series?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    boxplot = data.boxplot(column=['X', 'Y'], by='Series')
    plt.title('What is the difference between the four series?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        boxplot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
